        "orario": "16:36",
        "timestamp": 1773070565,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Jailed Istanbul mayor goes on trial in corruption case slammed as political Europe Issued on: 09/03/2026 - 16:36 Istanbul's former mayor Ekrem Imamoglu has gone on trial in Turkey on charges of corruption, in a landmark case widely criticised by rights groups. Imamoglu was arrested almost one year ago, when the opposition CHP party named him as their presidential candidate. Critics say the trial is an attempt to scupper Imamoglu's chances of beating Recep Tayyip Erdogan at the ballot box. 'This is all about defence': Macron addresses European security in Cyprus 09/03/2026 Europe Replay: Emmanuel Macron addresses Iran threat to EU member Cyprus 09/03/2026 Europe Europe rallies around Cyprus after Iranian strikes 09/03/2026 Europe Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East US and Middle East countries seek Ukraine's support in drone protection 05/03/2026 Europe Trump threatens to cut off trade with Spain over Iran war refusal 03/03/2026 Europe France to boost nuclear arsenal, could deploy atomic weapons to European allies 02/03/2026 Europe Europe 'exposed to the consequences' of US-Israel's conflict with Iran 02/03/2026 Europe Europe 'very likely' to get dragged into conflict after UK base in Cyprus hit 02/03/2026 Europe"
